==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nematoda
<hw>Nem`a*to"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A phylum of worms, having a long, round, and
generally smooth body; the roundworms. They are mostly parasites, in
plants and animals, but some are free-living in soil or water. Also
called <altname>Nematoidea</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nematode</ent>⟦br⟧
